How is it reasonable for drivers to act?

Other moral perspectives focus on how to make a big, fast strong car
(Vitalists of all shades), others are trying to find other content for
"good", from "helpful" to "good driver", "maximum miles driven for the
greatest number", "nice interior decoration and an awesome stereo", others
are indeed goal oriented ("HEaven is the way to go"), and some argue that we
should stop driving entirely (Quietists).

Yes, a nice analogy.

