The traffic engineer is indeed a "law giver," but not a tyrant. He is not
*imposing* any rules, but offering systems of rules for the consideration of
the drivers on the road, who may adopt and follow them or not. He is only a
systems analyst. He is consulted for his presumed expertise in the subject
matter, and his only enforcement tools are the clarity and cogency of his
reasoning.
